    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="670"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.248/1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-09T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 9, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—2:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>247. British training plane piloted by American flyer landed on Phoenix Park race
                    track yesterday. Pilot released and sent back to Northern Ireland. Plane to go
                    back today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
